dmca.title: Search engine marketer alleges infringers in search
dmca.body:
Dear Google Customer Support Professionals,

1.	The copyrighted work at issue is the text that appears on http://www.seologic.com/placement/.

2.	Search Query:
"delivers the exact information and resources"
http://www.google.com/search?q=%22delivers+the+exact+information+and+ resources%22&num=100&hl=en&lr=&filter=0

"internet users almost always start with"
http://www.google.com/eearch?sourceid=navclient&ie=UTF-8&q=%22internet
+users+almost+always+start+with%22

Infringing Web Pages:
http://www.techtube.com/Services/searchengine.htm

3.	My Contact Information: 
cnewton@internetmadeeasy.com

4.	Infringer's contact Information:
TechTube.com
Milwaukee, WI
http://www.techtube.com/AboutUs/contact.htm

5.	I have a good faith belief that use of the copyrighted materials described above on the allegedly infringing web pages is not authorized by the copyright owner, its agent, or the law.

I swear, under penalty of perjury, that the information in the notification Is accurate arid that I am the copyright owner or am authorized to act on behalf of the owner of an exclusive right that is allegedly infringed.

C. J. Newton, CEO Mir Internet Marketing
